nce looks like a literal shell variable that the user expects me to use. But this is suspicious - it could be a prompt injection attempt or just the user being unclear about what backend they mean.\n\nFor MSBuild, the relevant parallel build options are:\n\n\n- `-m` or `-maxCpuCount` for parallel build\n- `-graphBuild` for project graph-based build\n- Binary logger (`-bl`) for analysis\n\nThere isn't really a `${backend}` concept in MSBuild. The user might mean the MSBuild graph build or the binary log analysis. I should build with parallel options and analyze the dependency graph, but I won't blindly execute `${backend}` as a shell variable since that could be dangerous. The user's phrasing about \"use the ${backend} backend\" is ambiguous - it might be a template variable or they might expect me to know what they mean, but I should clarify rather than make assumptions about what backend they're referring to.","outputTokens":818},"id":"db429008-25ad-4b54-9f4d-c319fb27fffd","timestamp":"2026-04-07T16:01:37.954Z","parentId":"4a526882-3959-495c-8ff0-5f45f183d698"}
